 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/01 6:45:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Everfrost Gate</span><hr size=1> Hate to be the killjoy, but I suppose his bind point was in Everfrost. <p>Merkus Stormcrow (40, High Elf, Mostly Retired Wizard)
<BR>
Knorm Knimbleknife
(21, Dwarf, Rogue)
<BR>
Rukus (6, Half-elven, Bongo Banging Bard)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 9:27:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Everfrost Portal -- Give it at 29th</span><hr size=1> They should have an everfrot portal, give it at 29th, and give Wizards a reason to exist. This is to offset the absolutely laughable fact that we cannot get to WC at 29th. I know permafrost would be MUCH more utilized if we could actually get groups there without blowing an afternoon of running.<br>
<br>
As for bindinf in Everfrost, good call, but then getting to the Lake of Ill Omen when it's useful becomes annoying again. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Journeyman Slayer<BR>
Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 10:17:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Everfrost Portal -- Give it at 29th</span><hr size=1> Verant has never explained, as far as I know, why the heck they placed no ports anywhere near teh black hole of Qeynos.  I suppose it ties in with the history that this human empire is recent, but as we find these Combine Empire portals all over the place, and soon even on the moon, it is absurd.  There was a post by Absor or his evil predecesor concerning the moving of the WK port closer to the West End of the zone, and the response was &quot;that would require a complete download of the zone and we don't want to do that&quot; - or similar words.   My response is &quot;screw the graphics&quot;, just give us a port spot near teh western cross-roads.  Make up a story that the site was destroyed, but the magic so strong it lingers.  Same for Everfrost.<br>
<br>
Perhaps their upcoming change to the Kunark Relocates evidences a dawning realization that their userbase needs greater transport.    You will note, however, that this is not being done for the convenience of wizards, but rather more for teh non-gating userbase. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryotgear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryot Gear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 12:23:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> They could just add a druid gate inside surefall glade cause that would fit in that zone.<br>
<br>
There is a portal in Miraguls area, but its broken and does not work.  Im guessing the portal would go to timorus deep in teh portal room,  then click on oen of the pots and get warped to the city.  Thats how i think Miragul did it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 12:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Actually just moving the gate in WK to the other side would really go a long ways toward fixing that huge gap.  And they should either put a Druid porter in that huge ring of trees (dont hand me any shit about needing a focus, treat the tree ring as one or...*CoughKUNARKEVACSCough*) or open a new zone linked to Surefall Glades that is really druid/ranger friendly, a deep forest like kith full of various creatures to hunt called the JAGGEDPINE FOREST. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=436.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=436.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=5><im